      "writtenOn": "2021-07-14T08:03:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder if we should accept a default value here.\n\nUntil today, default values were set in yaml files in platform/tast-tests/vars. But a downside of this approach was that a runtime variable definition and its default value are described in far places.\n\nI remember that one reason we decided to put default values in yaml files was that we didn\u0027t have a central place for runtime variable definitions. For example two tests could declare the same runtime variable, and it\u0027s not obvious how to handle the case where the two tests declare conflicting default values. With the new proposal, we\u0027ll got a central place for a runtime variable definition, so we no longer have a problem.\n\noka@ WDYT?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 17,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 17,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "85fe8beb064852a12a2ef3a1563a20d8fd5bd1c2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9e0e57a0_75e1aaf6",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/testing/vars.go",
        "patchSetId": 21
      },
      "lineNbr": 17,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-07-19T05:11:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder how we can support secret runtime variables with that mechanism.\n\nCurrently the default values of secret runtime variables are defined in a private repository (tast-tests-private) with .yaml files. Tast CLI provides the values to public bundles if they are available at runtime. This is due to the requirement that the default values of secret runtime variables (e.g. passwords) must not be committed to public repositories.\n\nI think the point is that if we support secret runtime variables with RegisterVarString, there must be a way for public Go code to depend on private Go code, only when that\u0027s available. I\u0027m not sure if that\u0027s possible or not.",
      "parentUuid": "044588c9_d228f4cb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 17,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 17,
        "endChar": 35
      },
